Counter-Strike: Source : Bot's Navigation Mesh for the map DE_LIQUIDWEBX

Nav Creator: Meurglis3, Release Date: July 13 2017

Here is the Navigation Mesh for good designed industrial-themed map de_liquidwebx by neotic (released June 2007). It's a totally created fom scratch and fully hand-tuned .nav-file (in original mapauthor's release the .nav-file was almost unplayable).

This Navigation Mesh was manually remaded approximately for 80% 'cause auto-gen constructed many areas not correctly (also created many excess areas which are going beyond the map frontiers).

Well... Bots use all possible ways now and move according to all areas of this map quite surely. They frolic at offices of this liquid company as the real office plankton :D

Also this Navigation Mesh is fully Place Painted.

Play and Enjoy! All responses and remarks are always welcomed ;-)

Credits and Gratitudes: neotic (for nice fast-paced industrial-themed map).

Additional Gratitudes: BarnDoor (for perfect playable navigation meshes for many fine CS:S maps), Chizbone (for informative and clever article BOT_BRAINED and a set of excellent navigation meshes), CoCoNUT (for fine hand-tuned navigation meshes for many fine CS:S maps), Valve Developer Community (for learning articles by Navigation Meshes and Navigation Mesh Commands).

What a flies have stuck in this web..? :-)
